inline_comments.message:
I think you forgot to change the pattern to the format properly work:
"//*[@data-tests-id='%s']" <- this will find any element containing the attribute data-tests-id with the provided value %s;
Sometimes the code is using also "//*[@data-tests-id='%s']//*": this will find any child of the element found.

Maybe you should have something like this:

private static final String DATA_TESTS_ID = "data-tests-id";
private static final String FIND_ELEMENT_BY_ATTRIBUTE_XPATH = "//*[@%s='%s']";
private static final String FIND_CHILD_ELEMENT_BY_ATTRIBUTE_XPATH = "//*[@%s='%s']//*";

[...]
//this code should be wrapped in a method as it is called many times
String.format(FIND_ELEMENT_BY_ATTRIBUTE_XPATH, DATA_TESTS_ID, "desired data test id")
//or
String.format(FIND_CHILD_ELEMENT_BY_ATTRIBUTE_XPATH, DATA_TESTS_ID, "desired data test id") 
[...]
